NAME
    format_objects - formats a list of objects for humans to read
 
SYNOPSIS
    #include <acme.h>
    static inherit AcmeMisc;
    #include AcmeMiscInc

    varargs string format_objects( object *olist, status brief )    ;
 
DESCRIPTION
    Returns a nicely formatted bulleted list of objects and their
    short descriptions.  If brief is set, only pathnames will be
    listed.
 
EXAMPLE
    Sample output: format_objects( all_inventory(THISP) )
 
     0: /zone/null/toys/legchat/client#119       a LegChat v1.0
     1: /zone/null/toys/bin/wag#118              wag
     2: /usr/zippo/bw/bw#115                     beer
 
SEE_ALSO
    print_objects(A)
 
LAST MODIFIED                               
